        </details>

        <details class="group py-lg" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-md cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span class="text-body-md-strong text-ink" itemprop="name">How does it generate questions without an AI?</span>
            <span class="text-mute transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-md text-body-md text-body max-w-[680px]" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
            <div itemprop="text">
              Our PDF to quiz AI approach uses a rules-based pipeline: extract text with PDF.js, score key terms with TF-IDF across paragraphs, mask the highest-value term in each sentence (cloze deletion), and build three plausible distractors from the same document. It is fast, predictable, and runs entirely on your device without calling any external API.
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group py-lg" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-md cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span class="text-body-md-strong text-ink" itemprop="name">What about scanned PDFs or image-only documents?</span>
            <span class="text-mute transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-md text-body-md text-body max-w-[680px]" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
            <div itemprop="text">
              v1 does not include OCR. If we cannot extract any text from your PDF, the PDF to quiz maker will tell you immediately and suggest you run it through a free OCR tool first before using the converter.
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group py-lg" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-md cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span class="text-body-md-strong text-ink" itemprop="name">What file types are supported?</span>
            <span class="text-mute transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-md text-body-md text-body max-w-[680px]" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
            <div itemprop="text">
              Currently PDFs with selectable text. DOCX and Markdown input are on the roadmap for future versions of this free PDF to quiz generator.
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group py-lg" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-md cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span class="text-body-md-strong text-ink" itemprop="name">Can I edit the questions after they're generated?</span>
            <span class="text-mute transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-md text-body-md text-body max-w-[680px]" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
            <div itemprop="text">
              Not in v1 — but the source sentence is shown next to every question, so you can find and edit it in the exported file. An in-app editor is on the roadmap for the PDF to quiz maker.
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </PolarSection>

  <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is it really free? What's the catch?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "No catch. The whole tool runs in your browser, so we have no server costs to pass on. No account, no email, no credit card, no free trial. This is a 100% free PDF to quiz generator."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Does my PDF get uploaded somewhere?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
